         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[May 1874] ¶  ¶ You ask me, dear Dr Hooker, by last mail, whether I still hold Helmholtzia as a distinct genus. ¶  To this I must give an affirmative answer, as the matter presents itself to me in thi...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.05.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 146.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">[May 1874]<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg> MS annotation, apparently by Hooker: May 1874. This date is consistent with mention of the Educational Collections which, although apparently not distributed until September, were ready in June (M to T. Ware, 20 June 1874).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You ask me, dear Dr Hooker, by last mail, whether I still hold <name key="Helmholtzia">Helmholtzia</name> as a distinct genus.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> To this I must give an affirmative answer, as the matter presents itself to me in this way. If Endlicher had not separated <name key="Haeteria">Haeteria</name>,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Hetaeria</seg>? Endlicher (1836–40), p. 133.</p>
               </note> and if all subsequent writers on <name key="Philydreae">Philydreae</name> had not adopted this genus <name key="Haeteria">Haeteria</name>, then we could not well separate <name key="Helmholtzia">Helmholtzia</name>, though in habit it is more distinct from the two others, then these two are. if <name key="Helmholtzia">Helmholtzia</name> was not to stand, then it must go into <name key="Haeteria">Haeteria</name>, not into <name key="Philydrum">Philydrum</name>. In the allied orders of <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name> the shape of the anthers is of great moment; instance only <name key="Stypandra">Stypandra</name>. Of course it is quite possible that lower India<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The East Indies (i.e. Indonesia) and Malay Peninsula?</p>
               </note> and New Guinea may yield us additional <name key="Philydreae">Philydreae</name>, and then new changes in the genera may become possible; but as matters stand at present nothing is gained by uniting the three.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I thank you much for the sending of the second (volume or) part of the important "Flora Indica"<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1875-97), vol. 1, part 2, was published in January 1874 (TL2).</p>
               </note> What a treasure that work will be to Indian workers. The plants of Dr Tate are those of Hann's Expedition.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Thomas Tate collected during William Hanns 1872 expedition the Cape York Peninsula, Qld. See also M to J. Hooker, 8 September 1873 (in this edition as 73-09-08b).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I think you will find my limitation of the genera of <name key="Epacrideae">Epacrideae</name> the safest. I have in the VIII vol (pag. 52)<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B73.06.03.</p>
               </note> added to my former schema,<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B67.09.01.</p>
               </note> but omitted <name key="Cyathopsis">Cyathopsis</name> as a section of <name key="Styphelia">Styphelia</name>, besides <name key="Poiretia">Poiretia</name> ought to take precedence of <name key="Sprengelia">Sprengelia</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">but omitted … Sprenglia <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is marked in the margin with two vertical lines</seg>. Hooker treated the <name key="Epacrideae">Epacrideae</name> in Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 2, part 2, pp. 608-18, published in May 1876. His scheme followed that already published in December 1868 by Bentham (1863 -1878), vol. 4, pp 142-65, who had rejected Ms arguments against the groups and genera proposed in R. Brown (1810), pp. 535-56, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as unnecessary since M 'does not propose to remodel Brown's groups but only to reduce their value in the systematic scale, of which the principal result is an altered nomenclature' (p. 146). See Lucas (2003), pp 269–72.</p>
               </note> in all fairness, and to this view I have given effect in the first fascicle of the "Educational Collections" just to be issued.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to T. Webb Ware, 20 June 1874. For Ms Educational Collections, see Lucas, Maroske and Brown-May (2006), pp 34-6 and Maroske (2007).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Prof Agardh writes me that his <name key="Cycas%20">Cycas </name>has made new roots.<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">Letter not found.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Let your gardener examine yours.<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Hooker: Thank for <name key="Cycas%20">Cycas </name>Normanbyana. See also J. Hooker to M, 6 May 1873.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With best wishes</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
